observations.recommendation:
We have recommended that the Local Chief Executive:

Cease from granting cash advances unless the previous cash advance given to an accountable officer is settled or proper accounting thereof is made. Moreover, withhold the salaries of all accountable officers who are still connected with the LGU until the settlement of their respective cash advances; 

Require the Municipal Accountant to review and reconcile SL and supporting schedules with General Ledger/ Trial Balance and prepare complete SLs for cash advance accounts. Thereafter, send demand letters and instruct all accountable officers with outstanding unliquidated cash advances to liquidate their cash advances within 15 days from receipt or refund the full amount advanced, otherwise, administrative and criminal prosecution may be sought by management against individuals who fail to liquidate or refund the full amount advanced;

Instruct the Municipal Accountant to file a request for authority to write-off for accounts deemed dormant and liquidation is futile, following the procedures contained in COA Circular 2023-08 dated August 17, 2023; and 

In the case of those who have been separated from service, make representations with the proper prosecuting agencies of the government towards the institution of the necessary proceedings for the recovery of the amount of the cash advance as provided in Section 4.1 of COA Circular No. 86-256.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:

Consider reconstituting the manpower at the GSO office to avoid holding concurrent positions to fully focus their time and effort in the supply and property management of the LGU; 

Require the GSO and Municipal Accountant to prepare and maintain the Property Cards and PPE Ledger Cards and reconcile both records regularly;

Given the enormity of workload involving one time-cleansing of PPE, consider implementing the PPE cleansing by phase (i.e. by PPE class). Thereafter, require the Inventory Committee and the Accountant to submit to the audit Team the reports and documents required under COA Circular No. 2020-006 as appropriate, for verification.

We recommend that the Local Chief Executive:
Cease from granting additional cash advances unless the previous cash advance given to an accountable officer is settled or proper accounting thereof is made. Moreover, withhold the salaries of all accountable officers who are still connected with the LGU until the settlement of their respective cash advances;
Require the Municipal Accountant to review and reconcile SL and supporting schedules with General Ledger/Trial Balance and prepare complete SLs for cash advance accounts.  Thereafter, send demand letters and instruct all accountable officers with outstanding unliquidated cash advances to liquidate their cash advances within 15 days from receipt or refund the full amount advanced, otherwise, administrative and criminal prosecution may be sought by management against individuals who fail to liquidate or refund the full amount advanced;
Instruct the Municipal Accountant to file a request for authority to write-off for accounts deemed dormant and liquidation is futile, following the procedures contained in COA Circular 2023-08 dated August 17, 2023; and
In the case of those who have been separated from service, make representations with the proper prosecuting agencies of the government towards the institution of the necessary proceedings for the recovery of the amount of the cash advance as provided in Section 4.1 of COA Circular No. 86-256.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:

Require the Municipal Accountant to retrieve liquidation reports pertaining to the P13,300,000.00 completed projects and make adjusting entries as necessary, otherwise submit liquidation reports to the source agencies;

Require the Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer to return the unexpended balance of fund transfers to the source agencies. For balances with no identified source agencies, remit the funds to the Bureau of Treasury;

Identify details of the P12,438,310.43 fund transfer and project status and determine proper disposition of funds with reference to recommendation (b); and 

For accounts which remained non-moving for ten (10) years or more and where settlement could no longer be ascertained, instruct the Municipal Accountant to file a request for authority to write-off, following the procedures contained in COA Circular 2023-08 dated August 17, 2023.

